rawContent:
On 16 May 1944 more than 600 Roma and Sinti stood up to their Nazi capturers and refused to show up for the usual morning call at the “Gypsy family camp” in Auschwitz. This radical act of #courage and #resilience became the spark for Roma cultural and self-preservation and is memorialised as Romani Resistance Day.

This day reminds us of the importance of Roma Holocaust memorials, and the #EEANorwayGrants are proud to support the memorial in Lety🇨🇿, that held a memorial in remembrance of the victims.

The #EEANorwayGrants continue to support and empower Roma communities around Europe.✊
